[[File:SpannerA 2007-05-18.png|thumb|Spanner's main screen]]
[[File:SpannerB 2007-05-18.png|thumb|Spanner's 'about' screen]]

'''Spanner''' is a free program provided by [[Garmin]] for PCs running [[Microsoft Windows|Windows]] 2000 or XP. It ‘translates’ live positional [[data]] from Garmin’s proprietary interface into [[NMEA 0183]]. Garmin’s proprietary interface data is only provided via [[USB]] whereas NMEA data is provided via [[serial port]]. Spanner overcomes this by creating a [[virtual serial port]] and thereby allowing a USB based Garmin [[GPS]] receiver to ‘speak’ with programs that require NMEA data. For users with Windows 7 and above, GpsGate Client is required. 

Spanner is offered as a tool for Garmin’s GPS 18 product, but it works with other Garmin GPS receivers including the GPS 20x, GPSMap 60cx, 76CS, Colorado series (software version 2.51(beta) or later is needed), Oregon series, GPSMap 62/78 series, and Montana Series.

